@baseUrl = https://localhost:7293

### Anti-Cheat Warning System Test

### SETUP: Start an exam first (use existing exam session)
# Assume we have baithiId = 2 (from previous tests)

### 1. Log Tab Switch Warning
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/warning
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idBaiThi": 2,
  "loaiCanhBao": "TAB_SWITCH",
  "moTa": "Student switched to Google tab at 10:15:30"
}

### 2. Check Warning Count (Should be 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/2/warnings
Accept: application/json

### 3. Log Copy/Paste Warning
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/warning
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idBaiThi": 2,
  "loaiCanhBao": "COPY_PASTE",
  "moTa": "Detected Ctrl+C and Ctrl+V activity"
}

### 4. Log Right Click Warning
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/warning
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idBaiThi": 2,
  "loaiCanhBao": "RIGHT_CLICK",
  "moTa": "Student attempted right-click on question text"
}

### 5. Check Warning Count (Should be 3)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/2/warnings
Accept: application/json

### 6. Log Fullscreen Exit Warning
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/warning
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idBaiThi": 2,
  "loaiCanhBao": "FULLSCREEN_EXIT",
  "moTa": "Student exited fullscreen mode"
}

### 7. Log Multiple Tab Switch (Rapid violations)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/warning
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idBaiThi": 2,
  "loaiCanhBao": "TAB_SWITCH",
  "moTa": "Student switched to Facebook tab"
}

### 8. Check Warning Count (Should be 5 - Critical level)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/2/warnings
Accept: application/json

### 9. Log One More Warning (Should trigger auto-submit)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/warning
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idBaiThi": 2,
  "loaiCanhBao": "TAB_SWITCH",
  "moTa": "Student switched to YouTube tab - 6th violation"
}

### 10. Check Final Warning Count (Should be 6+)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/2/warnings
Accept: application/json

### 11. Check Exam Status (Should be auto-submitted)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/2/progress
Accept: application/json

### 12. Try to Save Answer After Auto-Submit (Should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/answer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idBaiThi": 2,
  "idCauHoi": 1,
  "idLuaChonDaChon": 1,
  "daLuu": true
}

### EDGE CASES

### 13. Log Warning for Non-existent Exam (Should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/warning
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idBaiThi": 999,
  "loaiCanhBao": "TAB_SWITCH",
  "moTa": "This should fail"
}

### 14. Log Warning with Invalid Type
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/warning
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idBaiThi": 2,
  "loaiCanhBao": "INVALID_TYPE",
  "moTa": "Testing invalid warning type"
}

### 15. Log Warning with Empty Description
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/exam/warning
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idBaiThi": 2,
  "loaiCanhBao": "TAB_SWITCH",
  "moTa": ""
}

